BOX MODEL----> it treats every element as a rectangular box.
properties of box model--
i) dimension(height & width)
ii) border
iii) margin: space between two elements .Short hand property means ek baar margin dene se 4ron side se margin aa jati h , hum ise jis side se dena chahein vo b kr skte hain like margin-top, left etc.
iv) padding: ek element k andar ki jagah ko padding kehte hain means element k border aur content k beech ka difference

**** ye sb sirf block element k liye use hota h , inline element pr work nhi krta ye(till now).

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

CSS Units.
1. Absolute Units -- ziddi hota h , screen size k according apne andar koi change nhi laata. 
2. Relative Units -- parent k respect m change hote hain.
     |
     ---> percentage
     ---> em ki vjh se snowball effect dekhne ko milta h , nesting hoti rehti h , aur uski vjh se child element jo h parent element ki properties ko inherit krte rehte hain.
     ---> rem: root element(html) pr depend hota h . isme snowballeffect nhi hota q ki ye fix hota h root element k according.
     ---> vh: view height: view port ki height k according chlega.
     ---> vw: view width: ---same---.


     vw, vh, %, ye hum dimension k liye dete hain like height and width.
     rem , em ye hum font size k liye dete hain.
     
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

DISPLAY_style--> box model to sorf block element pr work krta h, ab hum chahte hain ki hmara element inline element ki trh jitni need h utna space le , but agar hum use inline krdenge to box model wali property work nhi krengi , to uske
beech ka raasta nikala h i.e display:inline-block.
div{
    display: inline-block;
    width: 200px;
    height: 200px;
}
div:nth-of-type(2){
    /* display: none; */
    visibility: hidden; 
}
/* display none dene se vo element ko jo jagah di gayi thi vo vaapis le li jaayegi and the element will not be seen on the screen(invisible)  */
/* visibility : hidden wale case m spac(jagah) to occupy krega but blank dikhayi dega(invisible)  */




